      "short_description": "Super-Novae is a non-profit organization founded in France in 2021, dedicated to enhancing economic resilience in fragile and conflict-affected countries. The organization focuses on supporting local actors, youth, women, and marginalized groups through education, training, and social reintegration. Super-Novae has positively impacted 29,200 beneficiaries across five countries with a commitment to sustainable practices, including full carbon offsetting.\n\nThe organization operates through six key pillars: humanitarian aid, gender equality, development, innovation, environmental sustainability, and cultural initiatives. Its programs include vocational training, entrepreneurship support, and job matching, aimed at fostering economic growth and community resilience. Super-Novae collaborates with various partners, including the French government and local foundations, to implement projects that address the needs of vulnerable populations in conflict zones.",
